<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 12:58AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southeastern Surry and Stokes Counties through 130 AM EDT...
At 1257 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pinnacle, or near Pilot Mountain, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Walnut Cove...
Danbury...
Sandy Ridge...
King...
Pine Hall...
Pinnacle...
and Hanging Rock State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
